## RECOVERY PROCEDURE

### If Migration Fails:

**Option 1: Hard Reset** (DESTRUCTIVE)
```bash
# This will DESTROY all changes after the tag
git reset --hard comp-plan-v1-snapshot
git push origin feature/dual-ladder-migration --force
```

**Option 2: Create Recovery Branch** (SAFE)
```bash
# This creates a new branch from the snapshot
git checkout -b recovery-from-snapshot comp-plan-v1-snapshot
# Review changes, merge back if needed
```

**Option 3: Cherry-pick Specific Fixes** (SELECTIVE)
```bash
# Reset to snapshot
git reset --hard comp-plan-v1-snapshot

# Cherry-pick specific commits you want to keep
git cherry-pick <commit-hash>
```

